1-119.Certified public accountant; examination fee.

The board shall charge a fee as established by the board not to exceed two hundred dollars for the examination provided for under the Public Accountancy Act. An applicant for the examination may be required to pay additional fees as charged by and remitted or paid to a third party for administering the examination, if required by the board.

SourceLaws 1957, c. 1, § 14, p. 60;Laws 1976, LB 619, § 5;Laws 1976, LB 961, § 1;Laws 1979, LB 278, § 1;Laws 1984, LB 473, § 9;Laws 1991, LB 75, § 8;Laws 1997, LB 114, § 16;Laws 2003, LB 214, § 3;Laws 2009, LB31, § 9;Laws 2016, LB853, § 3.
